---
title: Pancetta and Chorizo Penne with Roasted Tomatoes and Creamy Red Sauce
description: Double the meat, double the cheese: that’s what you get with this rich, hearty pasta that uses both pancetta and chorizo as well as Parmesan and cream cheese. They’re tossed into a tomato-y sauce, fulfilling all of your pasta-night dreams. You can’t have all that deliciousness without a few veggies, of course, so we’re also adding juicy roasted tomato wedges and sweet peas.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/pancetta-and-chorizo-penne-8f26a6d9.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/pancetta-and-chorizo-penne-5addf61930006c5339780a52-0b727c36.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/pancetta-and-chorizo-penne-5addf61930006c5339780a52
nutrition:
  calories: 870 kcal
  fat: 45 g
  saturated fat: 21 g
  carbohydrates: 84 g
  sugar: 11 g
  protein: 35 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 1700 mg
servings: 2
course: main course
time required: 35 minutes
author: Michelle Doll Olson
cuisine: Italian
---

Wash and dry all produce. Adjust rack to upper position and preheat oven to 375
degrees. Bring a large #pot{} of @salt{}ed water to a boil. Cut @Roma Tomato{2}
into wedges. Toss with @Olive Oil{1%tbsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{} on a
foil-lined #baking sheet{} and arrange skin-side down. Roast until soft and
juicy, about ~{30%minutes}.

Meanwhile, mince @Garlic{4%clove}. Finely chop @Parsley{1/4%ounce}. Cut
@Dried Chorizo{3%ounce} into ¼-inch cubes.

Once water boils, add @Penne Pasta{12%ounce} to pot. Cook until al dente,
~{10-12%minutes}. Scoop out and reserve 2 cups pasta cooking water, then drain.

While penne cooks, heat a large #stainless steel pan{} over medium-high heat.
Add chorizo and @Pancetta{8%ounce}. Cook, tossing, until beginning to release
oil and crisp, ~{5-6%minutes}. Remove a quarter of the meats from pan and set
aside, then toss garlic into pan and cook until fragrant, about ~{30%seconds}.
Add @Tomato Paste{6%ounce} and cook, stirring, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add 1 1/2 cups
pasta cooking water and @Cream Cheese{2%ounce}; stir until well-combined.

Stir @Peas{4%ounce} into pan and allow to warm through, about ~{2%minutes}.
Season with plenty of salt and pepper. Stir in drained penne,
@Butter{2%tbsp}, and a pinch of @Chili Flakes{1%teaspoon} (to taste).

> TIP: Add more pasta cooking water, if needed, to give sauce a loose, saucy
> consistency.

Season with salt and pepper.

Divide pasta between bowls and top with roasted tomatoes. Sprinkle with
@Parmesan Cheese{1/2%cup}, parsley, and a pinch of chili flakes (to taste—you
may want to leave this off for the kids). Garnish with reserved chorizo and
pancetta.